OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1779948269
OL,3,CLondon Ambulance Services sees busiest
OL,4,Cday since the pandemic
OL,6,FAlison Blakely, our Deputy Chief
OL,7,FParamedic, said: "We want people to
OL,8,Fenjoy the weather but please take
OL,9,Fsteps to look after yourselves and
OL,10,Fothers around you.
OL,12,F"As the weather is set to stay hot for
OL,13,Fthe rest of the week, our message to
OL,14,Fthe public is to stay safe in the
OL,15,Fheat, drink plenty of fluids, avoid
OL,16,Fexcess alcohol, stay out of the sun
OL,17,Fbetween 11am-3pm and check in on those
OL,18,Fwho are vulnerable, including those
OL,19,Fover 65, young children and those with
OL,20,Fpre-existing health conditions."
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1779948269
OL,3,CLondon Ambulance Services sees busiest
OL,4,Cday since the pandemic
OL,6,F"Hot weather can have a significant
OL,7,Fimpact on people's health, and we have
OL,8,Fseen an increase in calls relating to
OL,9,Fdifficulty in breathing, dizziness and
OL,10,Ffainting, as well as more calls
OL,11,Frelating to chest pains and heart
OL,12,Fproblems.
OL,14,F"During the soaring temperatures we
OL,15,Foften see calls related to respiratory
OL,16,Fillnesses and cardiac-related calls
OL,17,Fare common in the days following a
OL,18,Fheatwave.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1779948269
OL,3,CLondon Ambulance Services sees busiest
OL,4,Cday since the pandemic
OL,6,F"Sometimes people start to feel ill a
OL,7,Ffew days after the hot weather so
OL,8,Fplease continue to look after yourself
OL,9,Fand others."
OL,11,FVisits to NHS web pages have surged as
OL,12,Fpeople sought advice on how to stay
OL,13,Fsafe in the hot weather.
OL,15,FWhile many people enjoyed the sunny
OL,16,Fbank holiday weekend, older people and
OL,17,Fbabies can be particularly vulnerable.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1779948269
OL,3,CLondon Ambulance Services sees busiest
OL,4,Cday since the pandemic
OL,6,FThere is also a risk of dehydration
OL,7,Fand heat exhaustion, which is caused
OL,8,Fby the body losing too much water and
OL,9,Fsalt, and can lead to heatstroke, a
OL,10,Flife-threatening illness.
OL,12,FNHS England said there were 20,092
OL,13,Fvisits to its heatstroke advice page
OL,14,Fon bank holiday Monday, compared to
OL,15,Fjust 488 the previous Monday. Over the
OL,16,Fwhole weekend, there were 36,724 hits.
OL,18,FElsewhere, people looking for tips on
OL,19,Fhow to deal with sunburn led to 5,342
OL,20,Fvisits to NHS webpages, with a total
OL,21,Fof 10,314 over the whole weekend.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1779948269
OL,3,CLondon Ambulance Services sees busiest
OL,4,Cday since the pandemic
OL,6,FParents also sought advice on how to
OL,7,Fkeep their babies safe, with visits to
OL,8,FNHS web pages for baby first aid and
OL,9,Fsun safety tips surging by almost
OL,10,F3,500% on Monday, with 4,728 hits.
OL,12,FDuncan Burton, chief nursing officer
OL,13,Ffor England, said: "While many enjoyed
OL,14,Fthe rare treat of a sunny bank
OL,15,Fholiday, the soaring temperatures have
OL,16,Fbeen of real concern for many new
OL,17,Fparents, with a 3,500% increase in the
OL,18,Fnumber seeking NHS advice for how to
OL,19,Fkeep their babies safe in the sun over
OL,20,Fthe weekend.
OL,26,@uD@TOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1779948269
OL,3,CLondon Ambulance Services sees busiest
OL,4,Cday since the pandemic
OL,6,F"Temperatures are now starting to ease
OL,7,Foff, but there are still health alerts
OL,8,Fin place for several parts of the
OL,9,Fcountry until 5pm Thursday, so it's
OL,10,Fvital that people stay on their guard
OL,11,Fif they're looking after those who are
OL,12,Fvulnerable to the heat.
OL,14,F"Babies, children, older people and
OL,15,Fthose with long-term conditions like
OL,16,Fdiabetes or heart problems are at
OL,17,Fhigher risk of heat exhaustion or
OL,18,Fheatstroke, so we'd urge people to
OL,19,Ftake care and to check on their loved
OL,20,Fones during these high temperatures.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
